#Text=The Utah Jazz ( 15 - 17 ) held off the Memphis Grizzlies ( 18 - 17 ) 92 - 87 in an overtime grinder Saturday night .
#Text=The strength of these two teams is defense and that was evident on Saturday .
#Text=It 's not just good defense though , as both teams have some of the worst offenses in the NBA .
#Text=There were still only 156 combined shots in an overtime game , which is indicative of the slow - paced nature of this matchup .
#Text=The major difference in the game was the free - throw shooting , as the Grizzlies hit just 54 percent of their free - throws on 26 attempts , while the Jazz made 75 percent on 28 attempts .
#Text=Memphis has had a rough season on the offensive end and this was as much of a struggle as any game thus far .
#Text=The bench really let the team down , as Zach Randolph 's eight points were the only points from the bench players .
#Text=Marc Gasol missed some crucial open shots that could have won the game , but he was still Memphis ' best player on the night .
#Text=Gasol tallied 20 points , seven rebounds and four assists in the loss .
#Text=These offensive struggles are simply too hard to overcome right now and it seems evident that something needs to change if this team will compete this season .
#Text=In any case , they 'll look to find some offense against the Portland Trail Blazers on Monday in their next game .
#Text=The Jazz have had an equally bad season on the offensive end , but they got a career game from an unlikely source .
#Text=Rodney Hood scored a career - high 32 points in the win and snatched down eight rebounds .
#Text=They 'll need him to continue playing like this with how thin they are at the shooting guard position right now .
#Text=Gordon Hayward also has a good game , as he tallied 14 points , five rebounds and four assists in a good all - around effort .
#Text=With all the injuries Utah has right now , they have to be somewhat satisfied still hanging around the .500 mark with players due back sooner rather than later .
#Text=They 'll look to build off this win against the Houston Rockets on Monday .
